title: Trump Dismisses Claims He Fell Asleep During Cabinet Meeting | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has dismissed claims he fell asleep during a recent cabinet meeting, insisting he was merely closing his eyes because the press conference had become “pretty boring.” Trump said photos circulating online likely caught him mid-blink, adding, “I don’t sleep much.” He also joked that Senator Marco Rubio would have woken him if he had actually dozed off. title: Nine Entertainment Sells Radio Stations To Billionaire Hotel Baron Arthur Laundy | 10 News+

title: Millions Of Epstein Files Released As Trump Named Repeatedly In FBI Material | 10 News
description: The long-running Epstein files scandal has taken a dramatic new turn.  Millions of documents - alongside thousands of photos and videos - have been released in what authorities say is the final public dump by the US Department of Justice.  Among the material, Donald Trump is referenced thousands of times, including in hundreds of unverified tips made to the FBI containing allegations of abuse.
